docs {
  # List Notifications

  Use this for the notification center screen.

  ## Endpoint

  `GET /api/v1/notifications`

  ## Query Params

  `page`
  Optional. Defaults to `1`.

  `limit`
  Optional. Defaults to `20`. Maximum is `100`.

  `status`
  Optional. Use `unread` or `read`.

  `type`
  Optional. Filter by notification type.

  ## Expected Success Response

  ```json
  {
    "notifications": [
      {
        "id": "...",
        "title": "Wallet funded successfully",
        "message": "Your wallet has been credited with NGN 990.",
        "type": "wallet_funding_success",
        "priority": "normal",
        "readAt": null,
        "seenAt": null,
        "emailDelivery": {
          "attempted": true,
          "successful": false,
          "error": "Brevo email credentials are not configured"
        },
        "pushDelivery": {
          "attempted": false,
          "successful": false,
          "error": "No active device tokens"
        },
        "createdAt": "..."
      }
    ],
    "pagination": {
      "page": 1,
      "limit": 20,
      "total": 1,
      "pages": 1
    },
    "unreadCount": 1
  }
  ```

  ## Delivery Status

  `emailDelivery`
  Shows whether backend attempted email delivery and whether it succeeded.

  `pushDelivery`
  Shows whether backend attempted push delivery and whether it succeeded.

  If login email does not arrive, check the latest `type: "security"` notification and inspect `emailDelivery.error`.
}
